node.text: get to head home for the holidays today to be with my beautiful family after such an amazing but exhausting year (hence the first pic where @claire_barey and @annibons decorated me while asleepüòÖ). anyways in cape town @claire_barey and i started talking about christmas with @niela_vd_poll who simply stated that christmas is a holiday to celebrate the birth of Jesus not to celebrate presents and gifts. we find ways to commercialize the holidays instead of spending them in love. growing up constantly training away from home i think christmas was the only time i had off to go home to see my family which is why this holiday is so important to me. watching my parents get older and seeing all the amazing people that have passed away this year, has reminded me that tomorrow is not guaranteed. so no matter where you are this christmas remind those that are important how much they mean to you and even take time to mend broken relationships that are worth it. hate takes too much energy and life isn‚Äôt forgiving enough to carry a burden. happy holidays! much love‚ù§Ô∏è
